\begin_layout Subsection
Oscillations for cognitive processes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Within recent years, a number of publications has related local control
 of cognitive functions in mammalian cortex to the interplay of 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

-range to lower-frequency oscillations 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
citep{Fries2015,Bastos2015}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 Experiments suggest that 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

-band activity from primary sources in the supragranular neocortical layers
 are a neuronal correlate of bottom-up processing of sensory information,
 whereas top-down control is represented by lower frequency oscillations
 from primary sources in infragranular layers 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
citep[Results, 2nd par]{Bollimunta2011a}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
citep[p4, upper left]{VanKerkoerle}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 In a series of hierarchically connected areas these differential bottom-up
 and top-down streams are beneficial, because activation representing an
 attended stimulus can be selectively prioritised for processing.
 Given the two distinct frequency bands, a prioritised stimulus can then,
 for example, be encoded in cross-frequency interactions, such as phase-amplitud
e coupling 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
citep[1st only mentions FA-coupling, 2nd describes the processing in streams]{Je
nsen,Spaak2012,Osipova2008,Jensen2014}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 The aforementioned concept for differential cortical processing streams
 is now widely accepted and establishes coherence between a number of theories,
 such as "Communication through coherence" 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
citep{Fries2005}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and "Predictive coding" 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
citep{Bastos2012}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 The perhaps most prominent example is the hierarchy of mammalian visual
 cortex 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
citep{Felleman91_1}
\end_layout

\end_inset

, where top-down control is mediated in the 
\begin_inset Formula $\vartheta$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $(4\mhyphen7\ut{Hz})$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

-band 
\begin_inset Formula $(8\mhyphen12.5\ut{Hz})$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
citep[focusses on theta, but Bastos 2015 also mentions $
\backslash
alpha$]{AndreMoraesBastos2015}
